The paper deals with algorithms for counting answer sets, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of dynamic programming and treewidth is a common technique in algorithms research, which suggests the paper could also fit into the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also deals with answer set programs, which are a type of logic programming, making the category of programming languages (cs.PL) a possibility. Finally, the paper discusses the exponential time hypothesis, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
